{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_2","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,240p' __issue_context__.json\"","aggregated_output":"{\n  \"body\": \"(This question was first raised in the [developmental stage ontologies](https://github.com/obophenotype/developmental-stage-ontologies/pull/102#discussion_r1799308335) repo, but as a side remark on a PR. It deserves its own discussion.)\\r\\n\\r\\nPart of the steps that are needed to build Composite Metazoan is to create “bridging axioms” that link the taxon-neutral terms in Uberon to their taxon-specific counterparts in the the taxon-specific ontologies (FBbt, FBdv, WBbt, XAO, etc.).\\r\\n\\r\\nFor almost all terms, that link is of the form:\\r\\n\\r\\n> {taxon-specific term} **EquivalentTo:** {Uberon term} _and_ ('part of' _some_ {taxon ID})\\r\\n\\r\\nBut for the terms that represent life stages (specifically '[life cycle](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0000104)' and '[life cycle stage](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0000105)' and their descendants), the links can use two distinct relations depending on where the bridging axioms are generated.\\r\\n\\r\\nFor the bridging axioms that are generated in the [life stage ontologies](https://github.com/obophenotype/developmental-stage-ontologies/) repository, they are of the same form as above (in particular, they use the same `part of` relation).\\r\\n\\r\\nBut for the bridging axioms that are generated in Uberon (typically, those are the bridges that link to externally maintained, taxon-specific life stage ontologies like FBdv or WBls), the links are of the form\\r\\n\\r\\n> {taxon-specific term} **EquivalentTo:** {Uberon term} _and_ ('occurs in' _some_ {taxon ID})\\r\\n\\r\\nwhere `occurs in` is [BFO:0000066](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000066).\\r\\n\\r\\nIt cannot be good that the relations used in those bridging axioms vary depending on the species (e.g. `occurs in` for _Drosophila melanogaster_, `part of` for _Gorilla gorilla_). Whatever relation is used, it should be the same for all species.\",\n  \"comments\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd86Sn3ix\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"gouttegd\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"@cmungall Two years ago you [suggested](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/2428#issuecomment-1103321518) that all links between Uberon terms and taxon-specific terms should take the form of two axioms:\\r\\n\\r\\n> {taxon-specific term} **EquivalentTo:** {Uberon term} **and** ('in taxon' _some_ {taxon ID})\\r\\n> {taxon-specific term} **SubClassOf:** ({relation} _some_ {taxon ID})\\r\\n\\r\\nwhere _relation_ would be 'part of' for continuants and 'occurs in' for occurrents. Is that still what you think?\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2024-11-06T14:37:11Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": true,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3409#issuecomment-2459924657\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd86a5ya5\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"ddooley\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"NONE\",\n      \"body\": \"I think 'in taxon' is the recommended relation now for attaching a life cycle to an (NCBITaxon) taxon class.  'in taxon' has no restriction on its domain.  (COB is moving to have life cycle be a subclass of process BTW).\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2025-01-17T17:21:44Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": true,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3409#issuecomment-2598839993\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd86a8DmS\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"uberon\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"yes, in-taxon\\r\\n\\r\\nOn Fri, Jan 17, 2025 at 9:22 AM Damion Dooley ***@***.***>\\r\\nwrote:\\r\\n\\r\\n> I think 'in taxon' is the recommended relation now for attaching a life\\r\\n> cycle to an (NCBITaxon) taxon class.\\r\\n>\\r\\n> —\\r\\n> Reply to this email directly, view it on GitHub\\r\\n> <https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3409#issuecomment-2598839993>,\\r\\n> or unsubscribe\\r\\n> <https://github.com/notifications/unsubscribe-auth/AAGZRCGZDF7LSH3LC5KKGJL2LE337AVCNFSM6AAAAABRISBU3CVHI2DSMVQWIX3LMV43OSLTON2WKQ3PNVWWK3TUHMZDKOJYHAZTSOJZGM>\\r\\n> .\\r\\n> You are receiving this because you are subscribed to this thread.Message\\r\\n> ID: ***@***.***>\\r\\n>\\r\\n\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2025-01-18T00:56:03Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3409#issuecomment-2599434642\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    }\n  ],\n  \"title\": \"What relation should link a life stage term to its taxon-specific counterpart?\",\n  \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3409\"\n}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
